CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 23, 1946, pg. 20, reads: "Thrill Capacity Crowd - Theresa L. Kaufmann Auditorium was filled to capacity Sunday evening when the Pittsburgh String Quartet was presented in a free concert. The performers, which included Julius Schulman, Max Mandel, Ernest Biel, Aaron Shapinsky and Robert Winrebe, played the works of Haydn, Mozart and Debussy. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh String Quartet including Julius Schulman and Max Mandel on violins, Aaron Shapinsky on cello, and Ernest Biel and Robert Winrebe on violas, performing in Theresa L. Kaufmann Auditorium, Hill District
